=head1 DESCRIPTION

Additional tax information associated with your TRN in Canada .

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CanadaQuebecSalesTaxNumber => Str

The Quebec Sales Tax ID number. Leave blank if you do not have a Quebec
Sales Tax ID number.


=head2 CanadaRetailSalesTaxNumber => Str

Manitoba Retail Sales Tax ID number. Customers purchasing Amazon Web
Services services for resale in Manitoba must provide a valid Retail
Sales Tax ID number for Manitoba. Leave this blank if you do not have a
Retail Sales Tax ID number in Manitoba or are not purchasing Amazon Web
Services services for resale.


=head2 IsResellerAccount => Bool

The value for this parameter must be C<true> if the
C<provincialSalesTaxId> value is provided for a TRN in British
Columbia, Saskatchewan, or Manitoba provinces.

To claim a provincial sales tax (PST) and retail sales tax (RST)
reseller exemption, you must confirm that purchases from this account
were made for resale. Otherwise, remove the PST or RST number from the
C<provincialSalesTaxId> parameter from your request.


=head2 ProvincialSalesTaxId => Str

The provincial sales tax ID for your TRN in Canada. This parameter can
represent the following:

=over

=item *

Provincial sales tax ID number for British Columbia and Saskatchewan
provinces

=item *

Manitoba retail sales tax ID number for Manitoba province

=item *

Quebec sales tax ID number for Quebec province

=back

The Tax Setting API only accepts this parameter if the TRN is specified
for the previous provinces. For other provinces, the Tax Settings API
doesn't accept this parameter.



